<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1895-11-29T23:59:59-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1895-11-29T00:00:00-05:00" n="748" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d748">
                        <opener><seg rendition="#center">[Telegram.]</seg></opener>
                        <head><hi rend="italic">Mr. <persName type="from">Williams</persName> to Mr.
                                    <persName type="to">Uhl</persName>.</hi></head>
                        <opener><dateline rendition="#right"><placeName><hi rend="smallcaps">Habana</hi></placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1895-11-29"><hi rend="italic">November 29,
                                    1895</hi></date>.</dateline></opener>
                        <p>Trial of Sanguily commenced yesterday noon; adjourned at 5 o’clock;
                            resumed to-day noon and finished at 3 o’clock. I attended as spectator
                            in compliance with instructions of Department. His advocate, Viondi, has
                            made a magnificient defense. Verdict not rendered yet.</p>
                    </div>
                    </body></text></TEI>